Set one year after BR1, the two surviving students from the previous year's bloodbath, Shuya Nanahara (Fujiwara) and Noriko Nakagawa (Aki Maeda) return home, their lives permanently scarred by the terrifying experiences of BR1. Around them, the Battle Royale act continues and another class is kidnapped and placed in a Battle Royale. After the previous incidents, the public becomes aware of what the Japanese government is doing to their children and riots break out, some people violently attacking Japanese politicians in the street. Democracy no longer exists in this Japan where the country is dictated by the Japanese military who came away from World War II victorious alongside Germany. The rioters are violently dealt with and their children are thrown in to Battle Royale along with the randomly selected tenth grade class of boys and girls.......


......Too bad the director Kinji Fukasaku lost his battle with prostate cancer and died during the production of Battle Royale II. His son, Kenta Fukasaku, co-director and scriptwriter of Battle Royale I and II has taken his place in directing the sequel to Battle Royale.

i'm feeling a bit down right now. i dunno why. today + my i.d. was officially confiscated for wearing a long-fucking-hair. + i didn't attend class because i have to get a temporary i.d. from SAO. (students something org.i forgot) + a concerned friend texted me that i changed na daw, in a negative way, that i have to be sensitive with my surroundings. + i went to our office to finish some paper works. + ariel and i had a meeting with thelma sioson-san juan, the general manager of abs-cbn publishing to finish the proposal and the costings for our upcoming show this feb. + dropped ariel at sequia apartment to meet-up with neil oshima. + went home. very tired. + chatted with several friends online while listening to jp's rants and raves with his 5th blowjob. =P + jp told me i look so worried. + had dinner with jp at jollibee. i had champ, fries and coke. hehe. yummm. sobrang busog. + jp went home + while walking towards the elevator. i saw this semi-cute small boy with a big bag, just got out of the elevator, stared at me.. while waiting for the lift, i look back, he's still there, few meters away, trying to make a phone call on a non-signal spot.. so i gave him a "will-you-stop-posing-there-and-follow-me" look, so he went back, just followed me. he looks pretty decent naman, so i'm not that worried. when i'm about to open my door. i greeted him. he said hi. me: u live here? him: nah. i just visited a friend me: what floor? him: 20th me: okay. see you around. + then i went inside, semi closed the door. grab a drink. then look again outside. he's near the elevator. then i said; u wanna come over? he said sure. + we just had a small talk. some getting-to-know-you type of conversation and as far as i can remember, he's a 23 years old freelance interior designer slash florist from makati. he also showed me his works on his cute laptop, which is not bad at all.. he had to leave early because he have meet daw his clients. ok. we just exchanged numbers. + took a nap for like two hours, feeling down, then i went online again. + phoned-up bing just to say hi. + my hickey still hurts from last night's ...

tangina sobrang badtrip ngayong umagang toh. papasok na sana ako ng classroom ko ng biglang hinabol ako ng guard then sinabi na "oi boss long hair ka na ah!" eh pucha ang ikli-ikli na netong buhok ah. parang high school leche. sabi ko i define nyo nga sakin ang long hair sa inyo? sinagot nila basta daw lumampas na sa collar eh long hair na. eh shet pala sila eh. shempre wala naman akong nagawa, kinuha nila yung i.d. ko, nde naman ako pwedeng nde pumasok kasi ngayon yung pasahan namin ng psychological report na pinaghirapan ko kagabi, hehe, pero babalik na lang daw nila once na magpagupit na ako. ahay. shempre badtrip ako, buhok ko to eh, pakielaman na lahat, huwag lang buhok ko. naglelesson yung prof namin wala akong natututunan. badtrip, iniisip ko kung ano pang gupit ang papagupit ko sa buhok ko. ayun nag quiz ng ten items, dalawa lang yung nasagot ko, hindi ko pa sure yung isa. panalo! 

ok natapos din yung first class ko, papunta na sana ako sa dad ko para kumuha ng allowance, sumakay na ako sa car ko, binuksan ko na, ayos, wala yung nagbabantay makakalusot na naman ako sa parking fee. iaatras ko na sana, pucha pagtingin ko sa likod may nakapark din palang sasakyan. ay puta araw ko ito. pagtingin ko sa car na nakaharang eh naka handbrake pa, pano na ako lalabas nyan, wala pa yung nagbabantay, whoo! gusto ko na sanang banggain sobrang inis ko e. naghintay ako ng matagal, hoping na dumating yung driver nung lecheng nakaharang na sasakyan. hindi na ako naka inip. umalis na rin ako, ginamit ko na yung natitirang money ko na pang-cab papunta sa dad ko. pagdating ko naman wala sha! panalo pa talaga dahil nde ko dinala yung atm ko. ansaya talaga, buti tumawag yung mom ko para sabihin na pahiramin muna ako ng money ng secretary ng dad ko. hayun. 

sana tapos na. wala ng dumagdag. todo na yon.

considering him as my so-called "older bro" is one of the best things happened to me, since apparently, i dont have one cuz i'm the eldest. i never expect this would last. all i thought he's always trying to make me feel better. all i thought he's unfeigned from what he's always saying. but no, all the while he's pressured pala from what he's doing to me. well he's not really obliged to do such things, like telling "good" things about me to other people, like they really care or interested. thank you, but it's not really helpful. he's so optimist. he'll compliment you to the fullest or anything positive even if (you really know)its not really you, just to make you happy and belong. it's kinda sad cuz it ended up just like that (i'm not gonna elaborate). (in my view) just a little misunderstanding. he said things that scathe me too much, like "i had enough of immaturity. it's time to be realistic and not play games". its like, in my view, those peaches and butterflies that he's imparting to me is not really from his heart. i just want to have a feeling of having a so-called older brother. am i demanding too much? i told him before i hate like promises, if we can't meet up with our needs, it's fine, mejo matampuhin ako, most of my friends knows that, pero sandali lang yun, mawawala din.. but he insist on doing his optimistic acts. parang, sana sinabi mo na yung asa loob mo before pa, look now, napuno ka na tuloy. i'm sorry and i thank you.

(jusko musta lang yung nakasulat sa msg. tinanong nya rin ako ng musta sa irc so dun ko na sha sinagot) me: heto mejo sabog, hang-over, mejo maraming nainom last night him: oo nga mukha nga, mukhang babagsak ka na (ummeffect yung pagaarte ko. shet.) me: oh, musta? him: ok naman, kaw? (kamustahan to death) me: so, so... aga mo nagising ah. him: d ako makatulog eh "then humirit ako ng.." me: ako ren, things are bothering me him: o what's wrong? me: ah uhm. can't tell. saka nalang. ehe. err. him: ok..its up to u me: (tinry ko i-divert) kwento naman. about u and matt? (fishing ito) him: hehehe i wont tell until u tel ur problem me: ganon. me: hmm, hmm wala lang. i miss you kasi. (tangnang hirit yan) him: ganun. me: oo me: o kwento pa? 'bout matt? him: wer goin out... me: yeah and? him: and wer liking each other na... (ouch pucha, nde ko nakeri) me: ok. (cinlose ko yung window nya, dinedma ko na muna, since nag memessage din kasi ako kay melvin sa face-pic) after few minutes, minack nya naman ako. him: kaw, mag kwento ka... me: heto may ginagawang novel sa face-pic, minemessage si melvin. sandali lang. him: aahhh him: minessage ako ni melvin... (yikes) me: ah o? ano sabi? him: may problema ka daw? me: ha? (dedma effect) him: sabihin mo yung problema mo pedi b...kung involve ako dyan me: uhm eh. him: tell me na? me: ok. to tell you honestly, ur sort of involve.... (sort of eh!) him: tell me na nga..... me: i like you, kaso late na to tell you. ur involve na with someone else..... d sha nag react ng matagal. then sabi nya. "aaahhh sorry". me: bakit ka nagsosorry? him: la lang. me: thanks nalang. him: bakit ka nagpapasalamat. me: la lang, i had fun hanging out with you. him: ako din. him: friends? me: yeah sure. (ek.) tuloy pa rin ang kwentuhan, dinivert ko na lang sa ibang topic, hanggang sa nag bye-bye sha kasi mag lulunch na sha. na-realise ko napaka immature ko pala noh or baka dahil immature lang sha. ewan ko. hay. buti nalang may friends ako. salamat. i'll just keep living this day like the next will never come. i can't wait to share another experience with another guy. i can't wait to fall inlove again. tomorrow will not be like today... tomorrow, i will be happy

Going Underground - which London Underground tube line are you?
I'm the CIRCLE LINE!
Your life has no direction. You run around and around and around, passing through many of London's tourist attractions, mainline stations and interchanges: as a result you are often overrun by tourists and accordion players. It takes you an hour to do one 14-mile round trip, passing through 27 stations. You are bright, cosmopolitan, and somewhat jaded, and you like accordion music. yes, i'm somewhat jaded and i like listening to accordion music ~~~
Who are you? ~~~
What obscure band are you? More on Mouse on Mars: Mouse on Mars, a German band, is probably one of the more unusual bands you are likely to hear. Alot of their music can be described as harmonized sound effects only cooler. It's definitely way out there, and on top of it the lyrics, which are minimal and not the focus point, are art-philosophy. Crazy, crazy stuff! I've only seen the video for Actionist Respoke, but it was really really cool ^_~ They are definitely a great band to watch an interview with, as they are outgoing, interesting, and have the cutest accents you will ever hear.
